The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Govt unveils Puja bonus

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Calcutta, Sept. 21: Over three lakh more employees will get Puja bonus this year as the government has raised the salary ceiling for eligibility.

 Employees with monthly emoluments of up to Rs 10,000 on March 31, 2007, will be eligible for the bonus. The earlier ceiling was Rs 8,300. Those getting between Rs 10,000 and 15,000 a month will be eligible for the festival advance. The range was Rs 8,300-12,000 until this year.

 The bonus and advance each Rs 1,000 will be paid within October 5, finance minister Asim Dasgupta said. Pensioners would get an ex-gratia of Rs 400. 

 Asked what prompted the decision, Dasgupta said: Our financial position has slightly improved. Over 9.3 lakh people will get the bonus this year. Six lakh got it last year.




